eigenvalues = pca_model.eigenvals
total_variance = sum(eigenvalues)
explained_variance = eigenvalues / total_variance
cumulative_variance = explained_variance.cumsum()

explained_variance_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Explained Variance': explained_variance,
    'Cumulative Sum': cumulative_variance
})

def find_components_for_variance(cumulative_variance, threshold):
    return np.where(cumulative_variance >= threshold)[0][0] + 1

components_75 = find_components_for_variance(cumulative_variance, 0.75)
components_80 = find_components_for_variance(cumulative_variance, 0.80)

print(f"Composantes nécessaires pour 75% de variance expliquée: {components_75}")
print(f"Composantes nécessaires pour 80% de variance expliquée: {components_80}")

In [ ]:
r2_df = pd.DataFrame(index=MA_normalised.columns, columns=['PC1', 'PC2', 'PC3', 'PC4', 'PC5', 'PC6'])
for factor in MA_normalised.columns:
    for pc in range(6):
        X = scores_df6.iloc[:, pc]
        X = sm.add_constant(X)
        y = MA_normalised[factor]

        model = sm.OLS(y, X).fit()
        r2_df.at[factor, 'PC' + str(pc+1)] = model.rsquared


r2_df = r2_df.astype(float)
print(r2_df)

for i in range(1, 4):
    pc = 'PC' + str(i)
    best_factor = r2_df[pc].idxmax()
    cumsum_factor = MA_normalised[best_factor].cumsum()
    cumsum_pc = scores_df.iloc[:, i-1].cumsum()
    print(f"Le facteur le mieux expliqué par {pc} est {best_factor} avec un R² de {r2_df.at[best_factor, pc]}")
    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(cumsum_factor, label=f"Cumulative {best_factor}")
    plt.plot(cumsum_pc, label=f"Cumulative {pc}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title(f"Cumulative Sum of {best_factor} and {pc}")
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Cumulative Sum')
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdts.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdts.AutoDateLocator())
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()

• it displays the value of funds based on traditional trading factors

• compute the returns of the fund

• construct the min variance portfolio, display its cumsum return

• At the begining of each month construct a portfolio using

– expected return : past month performance

– long only

– total allocation 1

– cannot trade more than 0.05 per factor

– each factor cannot be allocated more than 0.25

– total trading cannot be more than 0.15

• Display the PnL

• Do the same monthly optimization but this time you can get short and the GMV must be 1

Construct the min variance portfolio, display its cumsum return¶

In [ ]:
covariance_matrix_EQ = returns_EQ.cov()

def portfolio_variance(weights, covariance_matrix):
    return weights.T @ covariance_matrix @ weights


num_assets = len(returns_EQ.columns)
constraints = ({'type': 'eq', 'fun': lambda x: np.sum(x) - 1})
bounds = tuple((0, 1) for asset in range(num_assets))
initial_guess = num_assets * [1. / num_assets, ]
result = minimize(portfolio_variance, initial_guess, args=(covariance_matrix_EQ,), method='SLSQP', bounds=bounds, constraints=constraints)

min_variance_weights = result.x
portfolio_returns = returns_EQ.dot(min_variance_weights)
cumsum_portfolio_returns = (1+portfolio_returns).cumprod() -1

plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
cumsum_portfolio_returns.plot()
plt.title('Cumsum return of the min variance portfolio')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Cumsum Returns')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

In [ ]:
def calculate_portfolio_return(weights, returns):
    return np.dot(weights, returns)

def min_function(weights, returns):
    return -calculate_portfolio_return(weights, returns)

prev_weights = np.zeros(len(returns_EQ.columns))
portfolio_weights = []

for i in range(1, len(returns_EQ)):
    returns = returns_EQ.iloc[i - 1]
    constraints = [
        {'type': 'eq', 'fun': lambda x: np.sum(x) - 1},  # Sum of weights is 1
        {'type': 'ineq', 'fun': lambda x: x}             # Long only constraint
    ]
    bounds = [(0, 0.25) for _ in range(len(returns))]

    # Optimization
    result = sco.minimize(min_function, prev_weights, args=(returns,), method='SLSQP', bounds=bounds, constraints=constraints)

    if result.success:
        optimal_weights = result.x
        portfolio_weights.append(optimal_weights)
        prev_weights = optimal_weights
    else:
        print("Optimization failed for month", i)

prev_weights = np.zeros(len(returns_EQ.columns))
portfolio_weights_Short = []

for i in range(1, len(returns_EQ)):
    returns = returns_EQ.iloc[i - 1]
    constraints = [
        {'type': 'eq', 'fun': lambda x: np.sum(x) - 1},
        {'type': 'eq', 'fun': lambda x: np.sum(np.abs(x)) - 1}
    ]

    bounds = [(-0.25, 0.25) for _ in range(len(returns_EQ.columns))]
    result_short = sco.minimize(min_function, prev_weights, args=(returns,), method='SLSQP', bounds=bounds, constraints=constraints)

    if result.success:

        portfolio_weights_Short.append(optimal_weights)
        prev_weights = optimal_weights

        print("Optimization failed for month", i)
